node.text: We were honored last night to host Jennifer Merritt as our @krogerco Hometown Hero. Sergeant Merritt served for four years as a Generator/Operations Mechanic at Camp Lejeune North Carolina with the 10th Marines, Headquarters Battery. After her Service, SGT Merritt has worked tirelessly on behalf of the Women’s Marine Corps Association supporting female veterans throughout the United States, and currently serves as the Vice President of “Team Honor," an organization that supports Blue (Family Members with currently serving family)  and Gold Star (Families of the Fallen) Military Families throughout Michigan who have struggled due to loss and tragedy. For her exemplary service she has been awarded the Marine Corps Good Conduct medal, Navy commendation Medal and has been recognized for her selfless service by members of Congress and the United States. #OnePride
